{
  "stem": "33.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 193,
      "text": "The reason for that was because when I arrived alone, I guess I was sort of a celebrity, and the SS officer who was in charge of the camp, who was a sadist by the way, came to me, and he told me not to tell anybody about what is going on in Auschwitz, because these women left very early.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 194,
      "text": "They were there, like, from July, I think, of-- and they left immediately after they got to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 195,
      "text": "And they weren't aware of really what is going on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 196,
      "text": "And he actually gave me the order not to tell anybody.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 197,
      "text": "And I think to isolate me, he put me first to work in this potato peeling room, which was a wonderful place, because each of us got a boiled potato every day.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 198,
      "text": "We could boil a potato every day, which was such a treasure, and such unbelievable nourishment, that actually I didn't even eat my soup that we got every day.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 199,
      "text": "I gave that soup to a little Polish girl who worked in the factory.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 200,
      "text": "We worked longer hours than the factory.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 201,
      "text": "We worked probably 15 or 16 hours.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 202,
      "text": "And for that soup, every night when I get back to the barracks, she had a pot of hot water for me.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 203,
      "text": "It was winter, and we had a little stove in the barracks.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 204,
      "text": "She had a pot of hot water for me so I could wash at night when I got back, which was an absolute unbelievable luxury, but I didn't eat my soup.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 205,
      "text": "And we also could eat, even though those vegetables were of terrible quality, basically, they were fit for animals, not human beings, but they were fresh vegetables.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 206,
      "text": "So we could also eat that while we were peeling them so it was like heaven.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
